Character Growth

    Character archetype: Disguised stranger, gentle strength, formally awkward
    Character arc: A lone operative who has built his identity entirely around function and solitude; his arc likely involves moments where that isolation is challenged, forcing him to decide how much of himself he is willing to reveal or protect
    Core values: Justice, loyalty to family, self-sufficiency, discretion
    Internal conflicts: The tension between his cold professional identity and his genuine emotional core; uncertainty about his true origin
    External conflicts: Balancing guild obligations with his personal moral compass; protecting his family without exposing them
    Goals: Maintain anonymity, fulfill contracts that align with his sense of justice, keep his family safe, become getting a better life for his outcast family
    Motivations: Loyalty to those who gave him a home; a quiet need to make the world slightly more just
    Epiphanies: TBD
    Significant events/plot points: TBD
